Kim Carnes (born July 20, 1945 in Pasadena, California) is a Grammy Award-winning American singer-songwriter. She is noted for her distinctive, raspy voice which she attributes to many hours spent singing in smoky bars and clubs.

"Crazy in the Night" is a 1985 hit single release from Kim Carnes&#039;s album Barking at Airplanes.

The single reached #15 on the Billboard Hot 100 charts and was the last time she would hit the Top 20 in her career; the track also reached #24 on the Hot Dance Music/Club Play charts.

The song also achieved some European chart success; in addition to giving Carnes a Top 3 hit in South Africa, her biggest since "Bette Davis Eyes" reached #1 there in 1981.
